  <summary date="2021-06-11T14:55:50Z" status="Introduced in Senate">Climate Risk Disclosure Act of 2021

This bill directs the Securities and Exchange Commission to&#160;require an issuer of securities to annually disclose information regarding climate change-related risks posed to the issuer, including an issuer's strategies and actions to mitigate these risks.

Specifically, issuers must report their direct and indirect greenhouse-gas emissions and disclose their fossil fuel-related assets.</summary>
